                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                <head>No. 634.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Sickles</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 19, 1873</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Correspondence sent to London on the 16th is due there to-morrow. It includes
                    several telegrams which you may desire to have repeated; also the Spanish text
                    of the reply to our protest, which I hope you will order cabled in the original,
                    as it will best show the temper of this government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SICKLES.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
